eagle crest resort is a destination resort complex in the u.s. state of oregon. the resort has a large hotel, a conference center, three golf courses, and three major housing developments each with multiple subdivisions. the resort is located west of redmond in central oregon. the development covers 1,700 acres (6.9 km2) on the east slopes of cline butte running eastward to the deschutes river plus a separate area on the northwest side of the butte. the resort and the area around it is classified as the eagle crest census-designated place (cdp) and had a residential population of 1,696 at the 2010 census.